properties.Title: Blizzard Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Blizzard conditions with poor visibility in snow and blowing snow are expected or occurring. A strong low pressure system near Qikiqtarjuaq is giving some off and on snow today, however winds have remained relatively light. Similar conditions are expected this evening, however by morning north to northwest winds will strengthen in the 60 gusting 80 km/h range along with snow, blowing snow, and blizzard conditions. The blizzard will continue through Wednesday morning, with conditions starting to improve in the afternoon or early evening. During the worst of the blizzard, visibilities of 400 metres or less are expected in the area. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.
